  "response": "I'm sorry that you're feeling this way about your appearance. Remember that beauty is subjective, and everyone has their own unique features that make them special. It's important to focus on your positive traits and the qualities that make you a great person. Confidence and self-love are very attractive qualities. \n\nA person who is genuinely interested in you will appreciate and value you for who you are, beyond just physical appearance. It's also worth noting that people often perceive themselves more critically than others do. You might be judging your nose harshly while others may not see it negatively at all.\n\nBeing kind, confident, and true to yourself will attract the right kind of person who sees and appreciates your true beauty both inside and out.",
